middle; font-size: smaller; text-align: center; \" class=\"table-na\" | Contest cancelled{{Efn|The 2020 contest was cancelled due to the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]].}} '''X'''\n|}\n\n==Related involvement==\n===Heads of delegation===\nThe public broadcaster of each participating country in the Eurovision Song Contest assigns a head of delegation as the EBU's contact person and the leader of their delegation at the event. The delegation, whose size can greatly vary, includes a head of press, the contestants, songwriters, composers and backing vocalists, among others.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://eurovision.tv/about/organisers/heads-of-delegation/|title=Heads of Delegation|publisher=[[European Broadcasting Union]]|accessdate=27 May 2019}}</ref>\n{|class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\"\n!Year\n!Head of delegation\n!{{Abbr|Ref.|reference}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|{{Escyr|2008}}&ndash;present\n|Alessandro Capicchioni\n|{{center|\n<ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/entertainment/7365509.stm|title=San Marino's big musical moment|date=19 May 2008|accessdate=12 March 2020|website=bbc.co.uk|publisher=[[BBC News]]|last=Osborn|first=Michael}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://eurovision.tv/story/san-marino-spotlights-on-for-senit|title=San Marino: Spotlights on for Senit!|date=2 May 2011|accessdate=14 March 2020|website=eurovision.tv}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://eurovoix.com/2014/10/13/san-marino-the-peppermints-presented-to-public/|title=San Marino: The Peppermints Presented to Public|date=13 October 2014|accessdate=14 March 2020|website=eurovoix.com|first=Anthony|last=Granger}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://eurovoix.com/2016/05/26/san-marino-not-know-countries-decided-televote/|title=San Marino: Does Not Know Which Countries Decided Their Televote|date=26 May 2016|accessdate=11 December 2019|website=eurovoix.com|first=Anthony|last=Granger}}</ref><ref>\n{{cite web|url=https://eurovoix.com/2017/11/11/san-marino-600-applications-none-san-marino/|title=San Marino:Over 600 Applications, But None from San Marino|date=11 November 2017|accessdate=12 March 2020|website=eurovoix.com|first=Anthony|last=Granger}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://eurovoix.com/2018/12/30/san-marino-international-artist-eurovision-2019/|title=San Marino: International Artist to Represent San Marino at Eurovision 2019|date=30 December 2018|accessdate=12 March 2020|website=eurovoix.com}}</ref>}}\n|}\n\n===Jury members===\nA five-member jury panel consisting of music industry professionals is made up for every participating country for the semi-finals and Grand Final of the Eurovision Song Contest, ranking all entries except for their own country's contribution. The juries' votes constitute 50% of the overall result alongside televoting.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://eurovision.tv/story/exclusive-eurovision-2019-juries|title=Exclusive: These are the judges who will vote in Eurovision 2019|date=30 April 2019|accessdate=24 May 2019|publisher=[[European Broadcasting Union]]}}</ref> \n\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders sortable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! Year\n! 1st member\n! 2nd member\n! 3rd member\n! 4th member\n! 5th member\n!scope=col class=\"unsortable\" |{{Abbr|Ref.|Reference}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"| {{center|[[Eurovision Song Contest 2008|2008]]}} \n| [[Little Tony (singer)|Little Tony]] \n| {{Sortname|Vince|Tempera}}  \n| {{Sortname|Pasquale|Panella }}  \n| {{Sortname|Michele|Bovi|nolink=yes}}   \n| {{Sortname|Giuseppe|Cesetti|nolink=yes}}\n|{{center|<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.sanmarinortv.sm/news/attualita-c4/repubblica-san-marino-prima-volta-eurofestival-a84751|title=La Repubblica di San Marino per la prima volta all\u2019Eurofestival|language=[[Italian language|Italian]]|publisher=[[San Marino RTV]]|accessdate=17 March 2020|date=12 February 2008}}</ref>}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"| {{center|[[Eurovision Song Contest 2011|2011]]}} \n| {{Sortname|Sonia|Tura|nolink=yes}}  \n| {{Sortname|Massimiliano|Messieri}}  \n| {{Sortname|Chiara|